# NFC-Enabled E-Tourist ID Card — Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- **Backend**: PHP 7.4+ (procedural), MySQL via MySQLi
- **Frontend**: Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS, Font Awesome 6, Inter font
- **Hardware**: ESP32 + PN532 NFC RFID v3 (SPI mode, 115200 baud)
- **Server**: XAMPP (Apache + MySQL), project root at `/nfc`

## Project Structure
```
nfc/
├── includes/       # config.php, header.php, footer.php (shared)
├── assets/css/     # style.css (single file, CSS custom properties)
├── assets/js/      # app.js (nav toggle, photo preview, NFC Web Serial)
├── api/            # JSON API endpoints (nfc_read.php, nfc_write.php)
├── uploads/        # Tourist photo uploads
├── esp32_sketch/   # Arduino .ino file for ESP32 + PN532
├── database.sql    # Full schema + seed data
└── *.php           # Page controllers (index, about, login, dashboard, tourists, tourist_form, nfc_manager)
```

## Conventions
- Every page includes `config.php` first, then `header.php` / `footer.php`
- Use `sanitize()` for all user output (XSS prevention)
- Use prepared statements for all SQL queries
- Flash messages via `setFlash()` / `getFlash()`
- Auth check via `requireLogin()` on admin pages
- NFC communication uses Web Serial API → ESP32 serial at 115200 baud
- ESP32 protocol: `READ\n` to read, `WRITE:{json}\n` to write; responses end with `DONE` or `ERROR`

## Database
- DB name: `nfc_tourist_db` — tables: `admins`, `tourists`, `nfc_logs`
- Admin credentials: username `admin`, password `admin` (plain text)
- Tourist photos stored as filenames in `uploads/` directory
